like I was in a dream.

136
00:08:07,066 --> 00:08:09,000
After that,
I started catching...

137
00:08:09,068 --> 00:08:10,865
all your guest appearances
on Sullivan.

138
00:08:10,937 --> 00:08:12,871
I studied everything
you ever did--

139
00:08:12,939 --> 00:08:15,874
the way you built to your
one-liners, nice and relaxed...

140
00:08:15,942 --> 00:08:19,378
how you deliver jokes without
leaning too much on them...

141
00:08:19,445 --> 00:08:22,380
how you didn't say, ""Hey, folks,
here's the punch line.''

142
00:08:22,448 --> 00:08:25,042
You know,Jerry?
You know what I'm talking about?

143
00:08:25,118 --> 00:08:27,552
You don't say,
""Folks, here's the punch line.''

144
00:08:27,620 --> 00:08:29,815
You just do the punch line.

145
00:08:29,889 --> 00:08:32,221
Exactly. That's what
I loved about what you did.

146
00:08:32,292 --> 00:08:34,886
What I'm trying to say is,
now I'm ready.

147
00:08:34,961 --> 00:08:37,395
I'm ready, and--
I finished the course.

148
00:08:37,463 --> 00:08:39,897
