Mr. Gangetti, go right in.

497
00:27:28,760 --> 00:27:30,352
Hello? Yes.Jerry and I...

498
00:27:30,429 --> 00:27:32,863
discussed my being
on the show last night.

499
00:27:32,931 --> 00:27:34,865
He told me to call. Yes.

500
00:27:34,933 --> 00:27:38,391
Oh, sure. Sure.

501
00:27:38,470 --> 00:27:41,064
- [Wham]
- I'm supposed to wait.

502
00:28:17,075 --> 00:28:19,009
Is that cork?

503
00:28:19,077 --> 00:28:21,841
I don't know what it is.

504
00:28:21,913 --> 00:28:23,312
Is it dripping on you?

505
00:28:23,382 --> 00:28:26,317
No. I was looking
at the patterns.

506
00:28:26,385 --> 00:28:29,684
You know,
cork is good for sound.

507
00:28:31,089 --> 00:28:34,456
- It's very quiet in here.
- [Telephone Rings]

508
00:28:34,526 --> 00:28:35,618
Reception.

509
00:28:35,694 --> 00:28:38,822
No. You've got an hour
before they come in.

510
00:28:38,897 --> 00:28:42,355
No. He hasn't come back
from the meeting yet.

511
00:28:42,434 --> 00:28:44,368
- Mr. Pipkin?
- Pupkin.

512
00:28:44,436 --> 00:28:47,371
Sorry. I'm Cathy Long.
Can I help you?

513
00:28:47,439 --> 00:28:49,873
- You are?
- I'm Bert Thomas' assistant.

514
00:28:49,941 --> 00:28:52,034
He's our executive producer.

515
00:28:52,110 --> 00:28:54,544
Sorry. I've already spoken
toJerry directly...

516
00:28:54,613 --> 00:28:56,547
about my being on the show.

517
00:28:56,615 --> 00:28:59,049
He said to talk to him
personally.

518
00:28:59,117 --> 00:29:01,551
What is it exactly that you do?

519
00:29:01,620 --> 00:29:04,054
- I--standup comic.
- Where are you working at?

520
00:29:04,122 --> 00:29:05,487
I'm just working
on new material.

521
00:29:05,557 --> 00:29:07,991
As soon as you
start working again...

522
00:29:08,060 --> 00:29:11,496
call, and we'll send someone down
to check out your act.

523
00:29:11,563 --> 00:29:12,655
Thanks for stopping by.

524
00:29:12,731 --> 00:29:15,666
Jerry and I went over
all this last night.

525
00:29:15,734 --> 00:29:17,167
Does Jerry know your work?

526
00:29:17,235 --> 00:29:19,169
Yes. I don't think he does.

527
00:29:19,237 --> 00:29:22,001
You have a tape
I could listen you?

528
00:29:22,074 --> 00:29:24,668
A tape? Oh, naturally.
Whatever you'd like. Sure.

529
00:29:24,743 --> 00:29:25,835
Drop by a tape.

530
00:29:25,911 --> 00:29:29,847
I will. I can see
whyJerry would need that.

531
00:29:29,915 --> 00:29:31,007
Nice meeting you.

532
00:29:31,083 --> 00:29:32,516
Nice meeting you, too.

533
00:29:32,584 --> 00:29:35,417
This is really what's right.

534
00:29:35,487 --> 00:29:36,920
This is great.

535
00:29:36,988 --> 00:29:38,922
This is--
See you again.

536
00:29:38,990 --> 00:29:41,288
Nice talking to you.
Goodbye.

537
00:29:50,001 --> 00:29:53,095
Rupert. Hey, Rupert.!

538
00:29:53,171 --> 00:29:54,365
We've got to talk.

539
00:29:54,439 --> 00:29:57,374
What happened last night?
Did Jerry say anything?

540
00:29:57,442 --> 00:29:59,876
- Nothing happened.
- Did he talk about me?

541
00:29:59,945 --> 00:30:01,378
No. He talked about me.

542
00:30:01,446 --> 00:30:03,880
He must have said
something about me.

543
00:30:03,949 --> 00:30:05,382
Nothing.
What could he say...

544
00:30:05,450 --> 00:30:08,010
after what you did
in the car last night?

545
00:30:08,086 --> 00:30:09,781
You must be really loving this.

546
00:30:09,855 --> 00:30:12,790
Yeah. You were schmucko
supremo last night.

547
00:30:12,858 --> 00:30:15,793
I'm the schmuck? Me?
You're wrong, buddy!

548
00:30:15,861 --> 00:30:18,295
If I hadn't gotten
in that car last night...

549
00:30:18,363 --> 00:30:20,297
you wouldn't
have had the chance...

550
00:30:20,365 --> 00:30:23,334
to talk toJerry.
Keep that in mind.

551
00:30:23,401 --> 00:30:25,562
Not to be cruel,
but we're nearJerry's building.

552
00:30:25,637 --> 00:30:28,037
God forbid he
should see me with you...

553
00:30:28,106 --> 00:30:31,405
becauseJerry and I have a real
relationship, no fantasy world.

554
00:30:31,476 --> 00:30:33,410
After what you did last night...

555
00:30:33,478 --> 00:30:35,912
I don't want
to see you anymore.

556
00:30:35,981 --> 00:30:37,073
Fine! If that's what you want!

557
00:30:37,149 --> 00:30:38,980
Yes. That's what I want.

558
00:30:39,050 --> 00:30:40,483
Just get it to him!

559
00:30:40,552 --> 00:30:43,077
I'm not giving him anything.
No way,Jose.

560
00:30:43,155 --> 00:30:45,589
You're so friendly.
You give it to him.

561
00:30:45,657 --> 00:30:47,090
We're having
a communication problem.

562
00:30:47,159 --> 00:30:48,592
That's what you call it?

563
00:30:48,660 --> 00:30:51,595
You're always bragging about
how you broke bread with Jerry.

564
00:30:51,663 --> 00:30:52,755
Give it to him.

565
00:30:52,831 --> 00:30:56,767
Just do this for me!
I've done things for you!

566
00:30:56,835 --> 00:30:58,268
What have you done for me?

567
00:30:58,336 --> 00:30:59,928
What are you talking about?

568
00:31:00,005 --> 00:31:01,097
How about Howard Johnson's?

569
00:31:01,173 --> 00:31:04,336
I bought you food and coffee
night after night!

570
00:31:04,409 --> 00:31:06,536
You're crazy.
You didn't get me anything.

571
00:31:06,611 --> 00:31:08,704
- I bought my coffee.
- You never bought anything!

572
00:31:08,780 --> 00:31:12,045
I did things for you
that no money can buy.

573
00:31:12,117 --> 00:31:14,551
How about when
I gave you my spot?

574
00:31:14,619 --> 00:31:17,554
I let you get
right next toJerry!

575
00:31:17,622 --> 00:31:19,385
I waited for eight hours.

576
00:31:19,457 --> 00:31:22,893
You were crying because
you wanted next toJerry.

577
00:31:22,961 --> 00:31:24,053
You got next to him!

578
00:31:24,129 --> 00:31:26,563
What about giving
you my last album...

579
00:31:26,631 --> 00:31:28,064
of The Best ofJerry.!

580
00:31:28,133 --> 00:31:30,567
I didn't even
ask you for money...

581
00:31:30,635 --> 00:31:33,069
and I can't even pay my rent!

582
00:31:33,138 --> 00:31:36,574
I live in a hovel.
You live in a townhouse!

583
00:31:36,641 --> 00:31:40,577
O.K., you want to do that?
I got money for you!

584
00:31:40,645 --> 00:31:43,580
I can't believe how long
I've hung out with you...

585
00:31:43,648 --> 00:31:45,809
and listened to your tired,
stale, boring jokes.

586
00:31:45,884 --> 00:31:48,114
- Here's $900. No! No!
- Be quiet.

587
00:31:48,186 --> 00:31:50,381
Take this and give it toJerry!

588
00:31:50,455 --> 00:31:53,754
This is the last time.
This is the last time.

589
00:31:53,825 --> 00:31:55,383
When will he get it?

590
00:31:55,460 --> 00:31:56,586
Because you're a wacko.

591
00:31:56,661 --> 00:31:58,094
I'll know if you don't.!

592
00:31:58,163 --> 00:32:00,757
I know where you
and Jerry are.!

593
00:32:00,832 --> 00:32:03,426
I cover the waterfront!
Remember that!

594
00:32:03,501 --> 00:32:06,368
What are you looking at?
Beat it.!

595
00:32:06,438 --> 00:32:07,803
You scum.!
You're street trash.!

596
00:32:20,585 --> 00:32:22,519
First of all, Miss Long...

597
00:32:22,587 --> 00:32:25,078
thank you very much
for your help at the office...

598
00:32:25,156 --> 00:32:27,386
and for passing this
ontoJerry.

599
00:32:27,459 --> 00:32:29,825
I appreciate it
more than you know.

600
00:32:29,894 --> 00:32:31,054
Jerry, before I begin...

601
00:32:31,129 --> 00:32:33,563
thank you for listening
to this material...

602
00:32:33,632 --> 00:32:36,066
and for the opportunity
you've given me.

603
00:32:36,134 --> 00:32:39,069
Lots of people think
that people who've made it...

604
00:32:39,137 --> 00:32:42,573
lose their feeling for
struggling young talent,
such as myself.

605
00:32:42,641 --> 00:32:44,074
Now I know from experience...

606
00:32:44,142 --> 00:32:46,076
that those people
are just cynics...

607
00:32:46,144 --> 00:32:48,078
embittered by their own failure.

608
00:32:48,146 --> 00:32:51,411
I know,Jerry, that you are
as human as the rest of us...

609
00:32:51,483 --> 00:32:53,246
if not more so.

610
00:32:53,318 --> 00:32:55,582
There's no point
in going on about it.

611
00:32:55,654 --> 00:32:58,418
You know how I feel,
so let's get on with the show--

612
00:32:58,490 --> 00:33:01,084
The Best of Rupert Pupkin.

613
00:33:01,159 --> 00:33:03,389
Jerry, I've sketched out
this little outline...

614
00:33:03,461 --> 00:33:05,258
to save you time.

615
00:33:05,330 --> 00:33:06,524
It's a little introduction.

616
00:33:06,598 --> 00:33:09,032
So close your eyes,
imagine it's exactly 6:00.

617
00:33:09,100 --> 00:33:10,533
You're standing in the wings...

618
00:33:10,602 --> 00:33:13,036
and we hear Lou Brown
and the orchestra...

619
00:33:13,104 --> 00:33:16,267
strike up your theme song.

620
00:33:16,341 --> 00:33:18,536
[Theme Song Plays]

621
00:33:18,610 --> 00:33:20,544
And now, from New York...

622
00:33:20,612 --> 00:33:22,546
it's theJerry Langford Show...

623
00:33:22,614 --> 00:33:25,549
with Jerry's guests
Richard Pryor...

624
00:33:25,617 --> 00:33:26,982
Ben Gazzara...

625
00:33:27,052 --> 00:33:28,383
Elizabeth Ashley...

626
00:33:28,453 --> 00:33:29,545
Carol Burnett...

627
00:33:29,621 --> 00:33:32,215
and the comedy find
of the year...

628
00:33:32,290 --> 00:33:33,723
making his television debut...

629
00:33:33,792 --> 00:33:37,558
Rupert Pupkin,
the new king of comedy!

630
00:33:37,629 --> 00:33:38,891
[Woman]
Rupert.! Rupert.!

631
00:33:38,963 --> 00:33:40,828
-Are you crazy?
-Say hello...

632
00:33:40,899 --> 00:33:42,332
What's wrong with you?

633
00:33:42,400 --> 00:33:43,890
- People are sleeping.!
-Aw, Mom.!

634
00:33:43,968 --> 00:33:44,900
Lower it.!

635
00:33:47,138 --> 00:33:49,368
What's the matter with you?

636
00:33:49,441 --> 00:33:50,567
Mom!

637
00:33:50,642 --> 00:33:52,075
Take it easy.
Lower it.

638
00:33:52,143 --> 00:33:53,576
I'm not going to lower it!

639
00:33:53,645 --> 00:33:55,579
I have to do this now!

640
00:33:55,647 --> 00:33:58,081
I don't mind you playing it...

641
00:33:58,149 --> 00:33:59,582
but lower it.!

642
00:33:59,651 --> 00:34:03,087
Now, you come on,Jerry,
and you do your monologue.

643
00:34:03,154 --> 00:34:04,587
Then when the time comes...

644
00:34:04,656 --> 00:34:07,022
this is how
I see you introducing me.

645
00:34:07,092 --> 00:34:08,957
You could say
something like this.

646
00:34:09,027 --> 00:34:11,461
Will you please give
your warmest welcome...

647
00:34:11,529 --> 00:34:13,963
to the newest
king of comedy...

648
00:34:14,032 --> 00:34:16,227
Rupert Pupkin!

649
00:34:16,301 --> 00:34:18,963
[Applause]

650
00:34:19,037 --> 00:34:21,471
Good evening,
ladies and gentlemen.

651
00:34:21,539 --> 00:34:23,473
My name is Rupert Pupkin.

652
00:34:23,541 --> 00:34:24,473
[Laughter]

653
00:34:24,542 --> 00:34:27,477
I was born in Clifton,
New Jersey...

654
00:34:27,545 --> 00:34:28,978
which is north of...

655
00:34:29,047 --> 00:34:30,480
[Loud Laughter]

656
00:34:30,548 --> 00:34:32,482
Is there anyone here from...

657
00:34:32,550 --> 00:34:34,984
[Loud Laughter]

658
00:34:37,555 --> 00:34:38,988
But the fact is...

659
00:34:39,057 --> 00:34:41,992
[Laughter Swells]

660
00:35:11,523 --> 00:35:13,957
Mr. Pipkin...

661
00:35:14,025 --> 00:35:17,119
Pupkin. You'll get it
right one of these days.

662
00:35:17,195 --> 00:35:18,423
How are you?

663
00:35:18,496 --> 00:35:19,929
I'll bet you have a tape.

664
00:35:19,998 --> 00:35:22,831
- Right here.
- O.K. Got your name on it?

665
00:35:22,901 --> 00:35:25,199
We'll listen and get
it back to you soon.

666
00:35:25,270 --> 00:35:27,704
Thanks. When Jerry
finds a moment. Good.

667
00:35:27,772 --> 00:35:28,966
When will that be?

668
00:35:29,040 --> 00:35:32,601
Uh...Actually,
you can try me tomorrow.

669
00:35:32,677 --> 00:35:35,612
- Tomorrow?
- I might know something by then.

670
00:35:35,680 --> 00:35:37,978
- Otherwise, Monday.
- Monday? Hmm.

671
00:35:38,049 --> 00:35:40,609
What I might do
is just wait here awhile.

672
00:35:40,685 --> 00:35:43,119
MaybeJerry will find a minute.

673
00:35:43,188 --> 00:35:45,122
You're really
just wasting your time.

674
00:35:45,190 --> 00:35:48,125
We won't know anything
till tomorrow at the earliest.

675
00:35:48,193 --> 00:35:50,821
I don't mind.
I'm not wasting my time.

676
00:35:50,895 --> 00:35:53,830
I'm glad to do it.
It's important to me.

677
00:35:53,898 --> 00:35:55,832
- It'll probably be Monday.
- Monday?

678
00:35:55,900 --> 00:35:57,333
Monday.

679
00:35:59,070 --> 00:36:00,503
Well, I'll still wait.

680
00:36:00,572 --> 00:36:03,507
Really, I don't mind.
It's O.K.

681
00:36:03,575 --> 00:36:05,668
Tell you what.

682
00:36:05,743 --> 00:36:08,405
Why don't you try me
tomorrow afternoon for sure?

683
00:36:08,480 --> 00:36:10,414
- Tomorrow?
- Mm-hmm.

684
00:36:10,482 --> 00:36:12,416
- What time?
- 4:30.

685
00:36:12,484 --> 00:36:13,917
4:30. I'll be here.

686
00:36:13,985 --> 00:36:15,919
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

687
00:36:15,987 --> 00:36:19,013
- And thankJerry. O.K.
- I will.

688
00:36:22,360 --> 00:36:23,657
Goodbye.

689
00:36:28,199 --> 00:36:29,291
Goodbye.

690
00:36:32,303 --> 00:36:35,966
At least once in his life,
every man is a genius.

691
00:36:36,040 --> 00:36:37,473
I'll tell you something, Rupe...

692
00:36:37,542 --> 00:36:40,978
it will be more than once
in your life for you...

693
00:36:41,045 --> 00:36:42,137
because you've got it.

694
00:36:42,213 --> 00:36:45,148
From what I've heard here,
yeah, you've got it...

695
00:36:45,216 --> 00:36:46,649
and you're stuck with it.

696
00:36:46,718 --> 00:36:49,482
If you wanted to get rid of it,
you couldn't.

697
00:36:49,554 --> 00:36:50,885
It's always going to be there.

698
00:36:50,955 --> 00:36:54,118
I know there's
no formula for it.

699
00:36:54,192 --> 00:36:56,387
I just don't know
how you do it...

700
00:36:56,461 --> 00:36:58,395
and I'm not curious, mind you...

701
00:36:58,463 --> 00:37:00,522
because I want to use
the material.

702
00:37:00,598 --> 00:37:04,034
I'm curious because
I don't know how you do it.

703
00:37:04,102 --> 00:37:05,967
I really have to ask you that.

704
00:37:06,037 --> 00:37:07,095
How do you do it?

705
00:37:07,171 --> 00:37:10,607
I think it's that
I look at my whole life...

706
00:37:10,675 --> 00:37:13,109
and I see the awful things
in my life...

707
00:37:13,177 --> 00:37:15,611
and turn it
into something funny.

708
00:37:15,680 --> 00:37:17,113
It just happens...

709
00:37:17,181 --> 00:37:19,615
but what about
the first few one-liners?

710
00:37:19,684 --> 00:37:21,515
Were they strong enough?

711
00:37:21,586 --> 00:37:24,521
If they were any stronger,
you'd hurt yourself.

712
00:37:24,589 --> 00:37:26,022
They're marvelous,
you daffy bastard.

713
00:37:26,090 --> 00:37:27,717
Leave them alone.
They're beautiful.

714
00:37:27,792 --> 00:37:29,726
A man said--
Listen to me.

715
00:37:29,794 --> 00:37:31,284
Listen to me.

716
00:37:31,362 --> 00:37:34,331
A man said something
very profound some years ago...

717
00:37:34,399 --> 00:37:35,889
which I later originated.

718
00:37:35,967 --> 00:37:38,800
If it ain't broke,
don't fix it.

719
00:37:38,870 --> 00:37:41,270
Want to know how
I know it's so good?

720
00:37:41,339 --> 00:37:43,500
- Yes.
- 'Cause I envy you.

721
00:37:43,575 --> 00:37:46,009
I hate you, but I envy you...

722
00:37:46,077 --> 00:37:49,513
because it's purity, it's marvelous,
it's humor based on you.

723
00:37:49,581 --> 00:37:51,947
No one else
could do it, but you.

724
00:37:52,016 --> 00:37:53,176
I wouldn't lie.

725
00:37:53,251 --> 00:37:55,116
I wouldn't lie to you, Rupe.

726
00:37:55,186 --> 00:38:00,123
This weekend is perfect for you
to come to the house, if you care to.

727
00:38:00,191 --> 00:38:01,351
We'll hash it around...

728
00:38:01,426 --> 00:38:05,123
only 'cause I want to know
how you do it.

729
00:38:05,196 --> 00:38:07,289
There'll be people there,
but we can still work.

730
00:38:07,365 --> 00:38:09,265
It sounds great.

731
00:38:09,334 --> 00:38:12,303
- Terrific.
- I would really like to come.

732
00:38:12,370 --> 00:38:13,667
Could I bring somebody?

733
00:38:13,738 --> 00:38:15,797
Ayoung lady?

734
00:38:15,873 --> 00:38:17,864
A very special young lady.

735
00:38:17,942 --> 00:38:20,968
Of course.
I'd like to meet her.

736
00:38:23,548 --> 00:38:24,981
[Honk Honk]

737
00:38:25,049 --> 00:38:26,812
Hey,Jerry, how you doing?

738
00:38:26,884 --> 00:38:28,317
How are you?

739
00:38:28,386 --> 00:38:29,318
You're looking good.

740
00:38:29,387 --> 00:38:31,821
You should see me
in my white taffeta.

741
00:38:31,889 --> 00:38:32,981
Ha ha ha!

742
00:38:33,057 --> 00:38:35,082
You're doing some
great shows,Jerry.

743
00:38:35,159 --> 00:38:36,490
Thanks a lot.

744
00:38:36,561 --> 00:38:38,995
How about putting me
on your show?

745
00:38:39,063 --> 00:38:41,258
I could have used you
last night.

746
00:38:41,332 --> 00:38:42,356
Ha ha ha!

747
00:38:43,568 --> 00:38:47,004
[Whistling And Applause]

748
00:38:47,071 --> 00:38:48,971
- Hey,Jerry.!
- Hey,Jerry.!

749
00:38:55,580 --> 00:38:57,411
Come on down!

750
00:39:01,419 --> 00:39:02,852
Hi,Jerry, how are you?

751
00:39:02,920 --> 00:39:04,353
Hi, there.

752
00:39:04,422 --> 00:39:05,787
Morris, you will not believe...

753
00:39:05,857 --> 00:39:07,290
who's coming down here.

754
00:39:07,358 --> 00:39:08,791
Jerry Langford, right?

755
00:39:08,860 --> 00:39:09,792
Right.

756
00:39:09,861 --> 00:39:11,624
Oh, Morris, please hold on.

757
00:39:11,696 --> 00:39:14,130
Jerry, please sign
my magazine for me?

758
00:39:14,198 --> 00:39:16,132
- Yeah.
- You're wonderful.

759
00:39:16,200 --> 00:39:17,497
I've watched you
your entire career.

760
00:39:17,568 --> 00:39:19,502
You're a joy to the world.

761
00:39:19,570 --> 00:39:22,505
Please say something to my
nephew Morris on the phone.

762
00:39:22,573 --> 00:39:24,040
He's in the hospital and--

763
00:39:24,108 --> 00:39:25,302
I'm sorry. I'm late.

764
00:39:25,376 --> 00:39:26,809
You should only get cancer!

765
00:39:26,878 --> 00:39:28,311
I hope you get cancer!

766
00:39:28,379 --> 00:39:29,471
Jerry, an autograph?

767
00:39:29,547 --> 00:39:30,639
I can't. I'm late.

768
00:39:30,715 --> 00:39:33,115
I can't believe
that kind of a person!

769
00:39:58,843 --> 00:40:01,778
[Car Horns Honking]

770
00:40:37,615 --> 00:40:39,048
Yes, sir. Oh, hi.

771
00:40:39,117 --> 00:40:40,550
Hi. How are you?

772
00:40:40,618 --> 00:40:41,915
Not bad.

773
00:40:41,986 --> 00:40:43,453
Good. Good. I'm fine.

774
00:40:44,789 --> 00:40:46,222
Can I help you?

775
00:40:46,290 --> 00:40:49,555
Yes. I'd like
to seeJerry, please.

776
00:40:49,627 --> 00:40:51,060
You are...

777
00:40:51,129 --> 00:40:52,255
Pupkin.

778
00:40:52,330 --> 00:40:53,957
Rupert Pupkin.

779
00:40:55,633 --> 00:40:57,066
Mr. Potkin is here.

780
00:40:57,135 --> 00:41:00,070
That's right. O.K.

781
00:41:00,138 --> 00:41:02,538
She'll be with you
in a minute.

782
00:41:02,607 --> 00:41:04,541
Who was that?

783
00:41:04,609 --> 00:41:05,701
Miss Long.

784
00:41:05,777 --> 00:41:08,007
Oh, well...I'd...

785
00:41:08,079 --> 00:41:10,240
prefer to seeJerry.

786
00:41:10,314 --> 00:41:12,441
Miss Long will take care of you.

787
00:41:12,517 --> 00:41:14,883
O.K. I'll wait right here.

788
00:41:21,058 --> 00:41:22,525
And as a surprise...

789
00:41:22,593 --> 00:41:25,528
to Rupert being on the show
with us tonight...

790
00:41:25,596 --> 00:41:28,030
we'd like to present
to you someone...

791
00:41:28,099 --> 00:41:32,536
in a form that we've
never presented before,
a mystery guest.

792
00:41:32,603 --> 00:41:34,537
Please welcome
our mystery guest.

793
00:41:34,605 --> 00:41:36,539
Let's hear it for him.

794
00:41:36,607 --> 00:41:37,539
[Applause]

795
00:41:44,615 --> 00:41:47,049
Jerry,
this is the mystery guest?

796
00:41:47,118 --> 00:41:49,416
This is the mystery guest.

797
00:41:49,487 --> 00:41:51,352
Let's see if I can place him.

798
00:41:51,422 --> 00:41:52,480
I think I know.

799
00:41:52,557 --> 00:41:53,990
Don't you remember me?

800
00:41:54,058 --> 00:41:55,491
No, I don't.

801
00:41:55,560 --> 00:41:56,993
I'm George Cap.

802
00:41:57,061 --> 00:41:59,291
George Cap,
my high school principal.

803
00:41:59,363 --> 00:42:00,557
You guessed it.

804
00:42:00,631 --> 00:42:03,065
You used to fail me
all the time.

805
00:42:03,134 --> 00:42:06,365
What do you have him on for?
He's an enemy.

806
00:42:06,437 --> 00:42:07,495
Because you deserved it.

807
00:42:07,572 --> 00:42:09,005
-[Audience Laughs]
- Oh, thank you.

808
00:42:09,073 --> 00:42:11,007
I'm a justice of the peace now.

809
00:42:11,075 --> 00:42:13,202
- I perform weddings.
- Do you?

810
00:42:13,277 --> 00:42:14,676
[Band Plays Wedding March]

811
00:42:14,745 --> 00:42:15,677
Jerry.

812
00:42:15,746 --> 00:42:18,613
[Audience Applauds Wildly]

813
00:42:18,683 --> 00:42:20,014
Jerry, what are you doing?

814
00:42:20,084 --> 00:42:21,312
I can't believe this.

815
00:42:21,385 --> 00:42:23,683
Believe because
it's part of the surprise.

816
00:42:23,754 --> 00:42:24,846
How would the audience...

817
00:42:24,922 --> 00:42:27,356
like to see
the king of comedy...

818
00:42:27,425 --> 00:42:29,290
marry his queen
right here on the show?

819
00:42:29,360 --> 00:42:31,294
I don't know what to say.!

820
00:42:31,362 --> 00:42:32,795
Thanks a million,Jerry.

821
00:42:32,864 --> 00:42:35,230
That's too much.
That's too much.

822
00:42:40,438 --> 00:42:41,530
[Audience Laughs]

823
00:42:57,955 --> 00:42:59,980
[Plays Wedding March]

824
00:43:45,603 --> 00:43:46,627
Dearly beloved...

825
00:43:46,704 --> 00:43:49,036
when Rupert here
was a student...

826
00:43:49,106 --> 00:43:51,040
at the Clifton high school...

827
00:43:51,108 --> 00:43:54,043
none of us--myself...

828
00:43:54,111 --> 00:43:56,443
his teachers...
his classmates--

829
00:43:56,514 --> 00:44:00,041
dreamt that he would amount
to a hill ofbeans...

830
00:44:00,117 --> 00:44:01,550
but we were wrong...

831
00:44:01,619 --> 00:44:04,486
and you, Rupert,
you were right...

832
00:44:04,555 --> 00:44:07,615
and that's why tonight...

833
00:44:07,692 --> 00:44:09,489
before the entire nation...

834
00:44:09,560 --> 00:44:14,497
we'd like to apologize
to you personally...

835
00:44:14,565 --> 00:44:16,499
and to beg your forgiveness...

836
00:44:16,567 --> 00:44:20,003
for--for all the things
we did to you...

837
00:44:20,071 --> 00:44:23,507
and we'd like to
thank you personally...

838
00:44:23,574 --> 00:44:25,337
all of us...

839
00:44:25,409 --> 00:44:30,506
for the meaning
you've given our lives.

840
00:44:30,581 --> 00:44:36,520
Please accept our warmest wishes,
Rita and Rupert...

841
00:44:36,587 --> 00:44:39,784
for a long and successful
reign together.

842
00:44:41,926 --> 00:44:46,295
We'll be back to marry them
right after this word.

843
00:44:48,032 --> 00:44:50,466
- Mr. Pupkin.
- How are you today?

844
00:44:50,534 --> 00:44:52,525
- I'm fine.
- Good. Good.

845
00:44:52,603 --> 00:44:55,538
I want to thank you
for your tape.

846
00:44:55,606 --> 00:44:58,040
We listened to it
with great interest.

847
00:44:58,109 --> 00:45:00,543
We see a lot of good things...

848
00:45:00,611 --> 00:45:01,805
in what you're doing.

849
00:45:01,879 --> 00:45:04,313
We think you have
a very good potential.

850
00:45:04,382 --> 00:45:05,314
Good.

851
00:45:05,383 --> 00:45:07,248
Which is why
we're being honest.

852
00:45:07,318 --> 00:45:08,478
You should be.

853
00:45:08,552 --> 00:45:11,282
We just don't think
you're ready yet.

854
00:45:11,355 --> 00:45:12,481
Don't think I'm ready?

855
00:45:12,556 --> 00:45:14,285
Now you're not right forJerry.

856
00:45:14,358 --> 00:45:15,484
Right forJerry. Mm-hmm.

857
00:45:15,559 --> 00:45:17,493
Some of the material is good...

858
00:45:17,561 --> 00:45:20,325
but some of the one-liners,
for instance...

859
00:45:20,398 --> 00:45:21,558
are not very strong.

860
00:45:21,632 --> 00:45:25,363
In other words,
you didn't like some of the jokes.

861
00:45:25,436 --> 00:45:26,403
That's right.

862
00:45:26,470 --> 00:45:27,994
I can take care of that.

863
00:45:28,072 --> 00:45:31,508
Tell me the ones you dislike,
and no problem.

864
00:45:31,575 --> 00:45:33,873
That's a great help.
This is great.

865
00:45:33,944 --> 00:45:35,377
You have a good potential.

866
00:45:35,446 --> 00:45:36,913
Your timing was excellent...

867
00:45:36,981 --> 00:45:39,415
but you should keep
developing your act.

868
00:45:39,483 --> 00:45:41,747
Test it
in a few live situations.

869
00:45:41,819 --> 00:45:44,253
That would be very good for you.

870
00:45:44,321 --> 00:45:46,255
There are clubs you can try.

871
00:45:46,323 --> 00:45:49,019
When you start working
in one of those, call.

872
00:45:49,093 --> 00:45:51,391
We'll send someone
to see you. Promise.

873
00:45:51,462 --> 00:45:52,554
Thanks.

874
00:45:52,630 --> 00:45:54,598
- You're welcome. Bye-bye.
- Thank you.

875
00:45:56,901 --> 00:45:58,732
May I ask you a question?

876
00:45:58,803 --> 00:45:59,827
Yes.

877
00:45:59,904 --> 00:46:01,166
Are you speaking forJerry?

878
00:46:01,238 --> 00:46:02,330
Yes, I am.

879
00:46:02,406 --> 00:46:03,930
He has complete faith
in our judgment.

880
00:46:04,008 --> 00:46:05,976
I'm sorry to have
to say this...

881
00:46:06,043 --> 00:46:07,806
and don't take it personally...

882
00:46:07,878 --> 00:46:10,745
but I don't have faith
in your judgment.

883
00:46:10,815 --> 00:46:13,249
I'm sorry that
you feel that way...

884
00:46:13,317 --> 00:46:15,080
but there's nothing
we can do about that.

885
00:46:15,152 --> 00:46:17,552
I'm afraid I'll have to
disagree with you again.

886
00:46:17,621 --> 00:46:19,555
Well, that's your privilege,
Mr. Pupkin.

887
00:46:19,623 --> 00:46:20,647
Would you excuse me?

888
00:46:20,724 --> 00:46:22,419
I have a great
many things to do.

889
00:46:22,493 --> 00:46:24,859
Miss Long,
when willJerry be back?

890
00:46:24,929 --> 00:46:28,262
Mr. Langford won't be in
until very late this afternoon.

891
00:46:28,332 --> 00:46:29,765
We mean what we say...

892
00:46:29,834 --> 00:46:32,268
when we thank you
for coming...

893
00:46:32,336 --> 00:46:34,770
and we mean it when we say...

894
00:46:34,839 --> 00:46:37,171
you can call
when you start working.

895
00:46:37,241 --> 00:46:38,333
All right? Goodbye.

896
00:46:38,409 --> 00:46:39,569
Goodbye.

897
00:47:00,097 --> 00:47:01,689
Ahem.

898
00:47:03,100 --> 00:47:06,001
Is there anyone else
you'd like to see?

899
00:47:09,039 --> 00:47:10,973
No. That's all right.

900
00:47:13,043 --> 00:47:14,476
I don't mind waiting.

901
00:47:16,213 --> 00:47:19,478
Which reminds me about
the man who waited so long...

902
00:47:19,550 --> 00:47:22,018
he forgot what
he was waiting for.

903
00:47:22,086 --> 00:47:24,486
Well, would you mind
waiting outside, Mr. Pupnick?

904
00:47:24,555 --> 00:47:28,491
This is a reception area
and not a waiting room.

905
00:47:28,559 --> 00:47:30,493
I understand.

906
00:47:42,072 --> 00:47:44,006
You asked him to leave?

907
00:47:44,074 --> 00:47:46,008
Yeah, but he won't go.

908
00:47:46,076 --> 00:47:48,806
- What's his name?
- Rupert Pumpkin.

909
00:47:50,247 --> 00:47:51,976
- Hi.
- Hi.

910
00:47:52,049 --> 00:47:56,008
I'm Raymond Wirtz, in charge of security
for the Langford Organization.

911
00:47:56,086 --> 00:47:57,519
Let's go outside and talk.

912
00:47:57,588 --> 00:47:58,680
Is this your bag?

913
00:47:58,756 --> 00:48:00,189
Yes. I'm waiting forJerry.

914
00:48:00,257 --> 00:48:02,691
- We'll discuss that outside.
- I know he's expecting me.

915
00:48:02,760 --> 00:48:05,194
Listen, we'll talk
about that outside.

916
00:48:05,262 --> 00:48:06,627
Please take your bag.

917
00:48:06,697 --> 00:48:10,633
I'll explain company policy
to you on the way, O.K.?

918
00:48:10,701 --> 00:48:12,965
I'm pretty sure
you understand...

919
00:48:13,037 --> 00:48:15,471
that we have
certain rules here...

920
00:48:15,539 --> 00:48:19,635
that are essential to
the smooth functioning
of our operation, right?

921
00:48:19,710 --> 00:48:20,972
Right.

922
00:48:21,045 --> 00:48:22,979
Right. Good.
I can just say--

923
00:48:23,047 --> 00:48:24,139
Just listen, please.

924
00:48:24,215 --> 00:48:25,978
And that without these rules...

925
00:48:26,050 --> 00:48:29,486
we really wouldn't be able
to function at our best.

926
00:48:29,553 --> 00:48:30,645
You follow my point?

927
00:48:30,721 --> 00:48:32,655
I get the point except--

928
00:48:32,723 --> 00:48:33,815
Please, Mr. Puffer, please.

929
00:48:33,891 --> 00:48:34,983
No. After you.

930
00:48:35,059 --> 00:48:36,492
After you, sir, please.

931
00:48:36,560 --> 00:48:38,994
If I could just say thatJerry's--

932
00:48:39,063 --> 00:48:39,995
Just listen.

933
00:48:40,064 --> 00:48:41,497
I checked with Miss Long.

934
00:48:41,565 --> 00:48:43,499
You do not
have an appointment.

935
00:48:43,567 --> 00:48:46,001
Now, company policy is that
only authorized personnel...

936
00:48:46,070 --> 00:48:49,506
and those persons with official
business with our organization...

937
00:48:49,573 --> 00:48:51,507
are permitted on our premises.

938
00:48:51,575 --> 00:48:55,602
In other words, you want me
to leave the building?

939
00:49:19,737 --> 00:49:22,638
Well, did you get it to him?

940
00:49:22,706 --> 00:49:24,401
What?

941
00:49:24,475 --> 00:49:26,943
Did you get my letter to him?

942
00:49:27,011 --> 00:49:28,774
He's not in there, O.K.?

943
00:49:28,846 --> 00:49:32,509
Now that you're in with him,
you can't do me a favor?

944
00:49:32,583 --> 00:49:34,983
Don't bother.
Just give me the letter.

945
00:49:35,052 --> 00:49:37,520
- He wasn't there.
- I saw him go in.

946
00:49:37,588 --> 00:49:39,886
- Who?
-Jerry.

947
00:49:39,957 --> 00:49:41,652
He's up there.
Want to see him?

948
00:49:41,725 --> 00:49:45,821
That's impossible, because
they assured me that he was out.

949
00:49:45,896 --> 00:49:47,329
And you believed them?

950
00:49:47,398 --> 00:49:50,299
You're so naive.
I would expect that from you.

951
00:49:50,367 --> 00:49:52,699
You're so inexperienced.
You're such a chump.

952
00:49:52,770 --> 00:49:54,670
He went up there just now?

953
00:49:54,738 --> 00:49:56,330
Of course. Go back up.

954
00:49:56,407 --> 00:49:57,738
Assert yourself a little bit.

955
00:49:57,808 --> 00:49:59,207
He's up there right now.

956
00:50:11,021 --> 00:50:14,422
Would you tellJerry
I'm here to see him, please?

957
00:50:14,491 --> 00:50:15,890
I'm sorry. He's not in.

958
00:50:15,959 --> 00:50:17,859
I happen to know that he is.

959
00:50:17,928 --> 00:50:19,327
I'm sorry. He's not in.

960
00:50:19,396 --> 00:50:22,365
O.K., you're putting your job
on the line, lady.

961
00:50:22,433 --> 00:50:25,129
Security...

962
00:50:25,202 --> 00:50:26,669
You, too.

963
00:50:31,909 --> 00:50:34,139
[Telephone Rings]

964
00:50:48,625 --> 00:50:51,924
Mr. Pupkin,
what are you doing here?

965
00:50:51,995 --> 00:50:53,121
Mr. Pupkin.

966
00:50:54,231 --> 00:50:55,493
Mr. Pupkin.

967
00:50:55,566 --> 00:50:58,057
Shelly, get security
on the telephone.

968
00:51:05,042 --> 00:51:06,441
There he goes.

969
00:51:07,778 --> 00:51:10,212
Aah! Hold on, right.

970
00:51:10,280 --> 00:51:13,807
Grab his other arm.
Hold on to him, right.

971
00:51:13,884 --> 00:51:15,818
All right.
Right out the door.

972
00:51:15,886 --> 00:51:16,978
Come on.

973
00:51:17,054 --> 00:51:18,749
You wouldn't listen, eh?

974
00:51:18,822 --> 00:51:20,813
Jerry,Jerry!

975
00:51:20,891 --> 00:51:22,415
Nobody's going to help you.

976
00:51:22,493 --> 00:51:25,462
You're going to have a lot
of explaining to do, Mr. Wirtz.

977
00:51:25,529 --> 00:51:26,996
You had your warning, Krupkin.

978
00:51:27,064 --> 00:51:29,157
My lawyer will be calling you.

979
00:51:29,233 --> 00:51:32,066
Make sure
he gets my name right.

980
00:51:32,136 --> 00:51:34,468
Say goodbye to our guest,
Miss Long.

981
00:51:34,538 --> 00:51:36,403
Wait tillJerry hears about this.

982
00:51:36,473 --> 00:51:39,340
Don't worry. I will mention
your name toJerry.

983
00:51:39,410 --> 00:51:42,902
Now listen good, because
if we see your face again...

984
00:51:42,980 --> 00:51:44,174
I--I understand.

985
00:51:44,248 --> 00:51:46,182
We're going to call the police.

986
00:51:46,250 --> 00:51:47,239
Thank you.

987
00:51:47,317 --> 00:51:49,877
Thank you very much. Ha ha.

988
00:51:49,953 --> 00:51:51,887
- Terrific.
- Thank you.

989
00:51:51,955 --> 00:51:54,150
I suppose you got
the letter to him.

990
00:51:54,224 --> 00:51:55,589
No. I'll get it later.

991
00:51:55,659 --> 00:51:57,991
When?
You just got thrown out.

992
00:51:58,061 --> 00:52:00,825
I didn't get thrown out
of the building.

993
00:52:00,898 --> 00:52:04,299
Excuse me. I wasn't getting
thrown out of the building.

994
00:52:04,368 --> 00:52:05,892
You're a constant embarrassment.

995
00:52:05,969 --> 00:52:08,233
They walked me outside.
Just a moment.

996
00:52:08,305 --> 00:52:10,239
You can't handle
the simplest thing.

997
00:52:10,307 --> 00:52:11,774
I'll tell you something else.

998
00:52:11,842 --> 00:52:14,902
I'm going toJerry's for the weekend.
He invited me.

999
00:52:14,978 --> 00:52:16,411
That's how much you know.

1000
00:52:17,981 --> 00:52:19,448
Do I look O.K.?

1001
00:52:19,516 --> 00:52:20,483
You look wonderful.

1002
00:52:20,551 --> 00:52:22,018
Does this look all right?

1003
00:52:22,085 --> 00:52:23,450
That, I'm not sure about...

1004
00:52:23,520 --> 00:52:24,919
but you look wonderful.

1005
00:52:24,988 --> 00:52:26,216
What do you mean?

1006
00:52:26,290 --> 00:52:27,655
What's wrong with it?

1007
00:52:27,724 --> 00:52:29,988
I don't think you need it.
That's all.

1008
00:52:30,060 --> 00:52:31,994
You don't think it looks nice?

1009
00:52:32,062 --> 00:52:33,529
