I'm not fooling around.

1260
01:03:13,636 --> 01:03:16,161
What are you doing?
Are you crazy?

1261
01:03:16,239 --> 01:03:18,173
Get in,Jerry. Get in.

1262
01:03:19,175 --> 01:03:21,336
Hi,Jerry.

1263
01:03:21,411 --> 01:03:23,038
[Tires Screech]

1264
01:03:24,180 --> 01:03:27,149
She's going to hold
the gun on your head.

1265
01:03:27,217 --> 01:03:28,548
Don't make any false moves.

1266
01:03:28,618 --> 01:03:31,143
I'd hate to have to
do anything drastic.

1267
01:03:31,221 --> 01:03:32,711
Now, if everything
works out...

1268
01:03:32,789 --> 01:03:34,757
you should be out of here...

1269
01:03:34,824 --> 01:03:37,315
by the very latest,
1 2:00, 1 2:30.

1270
01:03:37,393 --> 01:03:40,885
Oh, maybe 1 :00.
1 :1 5 the very latest.

1271
01:03:40,964 --> 01:03:43,933
What I want you to do
is call your producer.

1272
01:03:44,000 --> 01:03:45,160
Call what?

1273
01:03:45,235 --> 01:03:48,170
Bert Thomas.
I want you to call him.

1274
01:03:48,238 --> 01:03:50,172
I'll give you the phone now.

1275
01:03:50,240 --> 01:03:51,707
Get him on the phone...

1276
01:03:51,774 --> 01:03:55,210
and I'll tell you
exactly what to say, O.K.?

1277
01:03:56,646 --> 01:03:58,580
Now, if you don't do it...

1278
01:03:58,648 --> 01:04:00,809
I don't know what to say.

1279
01:04:00,884 --> 01:04:02,818
There could be a problem.

1280
01:04:04,220 --> 01:04:05,619
Now watch your eyes,Jerry.

1281
01:04:05,688 --> 01:04:08,179
I'm going to take these off now.

1282
01:04:08,258 --> 01:04:10,726
It's a little
bright in here, O.K.?

1283
01:04:25,275 --> 01:04:26,401
O.K.

1284
01:04:31,347 --> 01:04:32,780
Are these yours?

1285
01:04:34,184 --> 01:04:35,549
Jerry, these are yours?

1286
01:04:35,618 --> 01:04:36,710
Yeah.

1287
01:04:36,786 --> 01:04:39,186
Do you mind if I have one?

1288
01:04:39,255 --> 01:04:42,418
- I don't mind.
- Thank you.

1289
01:04:42,492 --> 01:04:44,619
- Masha, do you want one?
- Save it for me.

1290
01:04:44,694 --> 01:04:46,127
You want one?

1291
01:04:46,196 --> 01:04:49,188
Yeah, I'd love one,
but will you save it?

1292
01:04:49,265 --> 01:04:51,699
It's a little inconvenient
at the moment.

1293
01:04:51,768 --> 01:04:53,167
Do you want one?

1294
01:04:53,236 --> 01:04:54,396
No.

1295
01:04:54,470 --> 01:04:57,200
I'll just take one
for later, then.

1296
01:04:58,675 --> 01:05:01,701
You know, there's no reason
to get mad about it.

1297
01:05:01,778 --> 01:05:04,144
I'm just trying
to ease the tension.

1298
01:05:04,214 --> 01:05:06,580
Even though this is
a strange situation...

1299
01:05:06,649 --> 01:05:08,082
there are moments
of friendship...

1300
01:05:08,151 --> 01:05:10,676
and moments of sharing,
or whatever.

1301
01:05:10,753 --> 01:05:12,152
O.K., let's go.

1302
01:05:16,693 --> 01:05:18,217
Jerry, I mean business.

1303
01:05:18,294 --> 01:05:20,455
Get on the phone.
Let's go.

1304
01:05:20,530 --> 01:05:22,259
The fun is over.

1305
01:05:25,635 --> 01:05:27,296
Let's go. Come on.

1306
01:05:43,119 --> 01:05:46,850
Bert Thomas, please.
Jerry Langford.

1307
01:05:50,360 --> 01:05:51,657
What happened?

1308
01:05:51,728 --> 01:05:53,059
They hung up.

1309
01:05:56,866 --> 01:05:57,992
Call them again.

1310
01:05:58,067 --> 01:05:59,694
Why did they hang up?

1311
01:05:59,769 --> 01:06:01,669
Probably thought it was a gag.

1312
01:06:01,738 --> 01:06:03,706
We get that all the time.

1313
01:06:03,773 --> 01:06:05,206
Well, I find that strange...

1314
01:06:05,275 --> 01:06:06,936
but it's typical...

1315
01:06:07,010 --> 01:06:09,911
'cause that's the way
they treat even you...

1316
01:06:09,979 --> 01:06:12,914
'cause I'll let you in
on a little secret.

1317
01:06:12,982 --> 01:06:16,076
That's the way
they treated me...

1318
01:06:16,152 --> 01:06:18,450
and now look where we are.

1319
01:06:21,324 --> 01:06:22,882
Bert Thomas.

1320
01:06:22,959 --> 01:06:24,358
Audrey, this is Jerry Langford.

1321
01:06:24,427 --> 01:06:26,554
Get Bert Thomas
on the phone quickly.

1322
01:06:26,629 --> 01:06:29,655
I'm too busy for fun
and games today. Goodbye.

1323
01:06:29,732 --> 01:06:31,632
Did you hear what I said?

1324
01:06:31,701 --> 01:06:33,168
This is Jerry Langford.

1325
01:06:33,236 --> 01:06:35,966
Get Bert Thomas.
This is serious. Now move it.

1326
01:06:38,841 --> 01:06:40,741
Why don't we have
somebody else?

1327
01:06:40,810 --> 01:06:41,799
Like what?

1328
01:06:41,878 --> 01:06:44,244
It's Mr. Langford.
He says it's urgent.

1329
01:06:44,314 --> 01:06:47,750
Tell him I'll call him back.
I'm busy.

1330
01:06:47,817 --> 01:06:49,648
It's that Martino kid
the impressionist.

1331
01:06:49,719 --> 01:06:50,845
O.K.

1332
01:06:50,920 --> 01:06:52,945
Will you do what I tell you?

1333
01:06:53,022 --> 01:06:54,148
Do it quick.

1334
01:06:54,223 --> 01:06:56,020
I'm sorry, Mr. Thomas.

1335
01:06:56,092 --> 01:06:58,560
He absolutely insists
on talking to you.

1336
01:06:58,628 --> 01:07:00,061
O.K., I'll take it.

1337
01:07:03,232 --> 01:07:05,325
Martino,
you know better than--

1338
01:07:05,401 --> 01:07:07,266
Bert, I said this is Jerry.

1339
01:07:07,337 --> 01:07:10,363
Jerry Langford,
and I'm in deep trouble.

1340
01:07:10,440 --> 01:07:12,465
Now, you'd best pay attention.

1341
01:07:12,542 --> 01:07:14,271
Yeah. I am listening.

1342
01:07:17,680 --> 01:07:20,148
Would you give me that again?

1343
01:07:23,219 --> 01:07:25,016
Now, wait a minute.

1344
01:07:25,088 --> 01:07:27,181
Um, I want to
ask you something.

1345
01:07:27,256 --> 01:07:31,056
What do we call our
second camera man?

1346
01:07:31,127 --> 01:07:34,858
We call our second camera man
Helen Keller.

1347
01:07:37,133 --> 01:07:39,067
His favorite color is plaid.

1348
01:07:39,135 --> 01:07:41,968
Helen Keller, plaid?
What is that?

1349
01:07:42,038 --> 01:07:44,438
When someone imitates me
on the phone...

1350
01:07:44,507 --> 01:07:48,443
the only way they know
it's me is by that clue.

1351
01:07:48,511 --> 01:07:52,072
And if I didn't know
the name we call him--

1352
01:07:52,148 --> 01:07:53,615
Say no more.
I understand.

1353
01:07:53,683 --> 01:07:57,312
Now, listen, Bert.
Listen carefully.

1354
01:07:59,122 --> 01:08:00,612
""I have a gun...''

1355
01:08:03,693 --> 01:08:04,751
""at my head.''

1356
01:08:07,463 --> 01:08:11,024
""If a man who identifies himself as...''

1357
01:08:15,505 --> 01:08:17,939
""the king...''

1358
01:08:22,111 --> 01:08:23,976
The card's upside down.

1359
01:08:25,982 --> 01:08:27,210
Sorry.

1360
01:08:28,785 --> 01:08:32,551
""Is not allowed to be
the first guest on...''

1361
01:08:37,894 --> 01:08:40,328
You got a blank card there.

1362
01:08:40,396 --> 01:08:41,988
Hold on, Bert.

1363
01:08:42,064 --> 01:08:44,862
I'm reading from cue cards.

1364
01:08:49,539 --> 01:08:51,507
"Tonight's show... '

1365
01:08:54,210 --> 01:08:57,577
"you'll never see me... '

1366
01:09:00,082 --> 01:09:01,845
Go back.

1367
01:09:01,918 --> 01:09:05,046
"Alive again. '

1368
01:09:06,989 --> 01:09:08,650
It--it's not
grammatically correct...

1369
01:09:08,724 --> 01:09:11,693
but I think you have the idea.

1370
01:09:11,761 --> 01:09:14,730
It's clear, but let me
break in for a minute.

1371
01:09:14,797 --> 01:09:16,264
Don't you do anything silly.

1372
01:09:16,332 --> 01:09:18,823
O.K., I'm O.K.

1373
01:09:18,901 --> 01:09:21,893
I'm O.K., Bert.
Just get it done.

1374
01:09:24,340 --> 01:09:26,808
He wants you to call at 5:00.

1375
01:09:26,876 --> 01:09:28,844
I'll give you
the private number...

1376
01:09:28,911 --> 01:09:30,811
and they'll do
whatever you want.

1377
01:09:30,880 --> 01:09:32,848
O.K., that was very good,Jerry.

1378
01:09:32,915 --> 01:09:35,179
Turn around
and see how it looks.

1379
01:09:35,251 --> 01:09:37,481
Oh, I love it.

1380
01:09:37,553 --> 01:09:39,885
I'm sorry. The sleeves
aren't quite right.

1381
01:09:39,956 --> 01:09:41,890
Do you like it on him?

1382
01:09:41,958 --> 01:09:43,516
What do you think?

1383
01:09:43,593 --> 01:09:45,959
I think it looks pretty good.

1384
01:09:46,028 --> 01:09:48,519
To guess on it,
have it turn out like this.

1385
01:09:48,598 --> 01:09:49,895
I'm very pleased with it.

1386
01:09:49,966 --> 01:09:51,194
The color's great.

1387
01:09:51,267 --> 01:09:55,101
I like to see him
a little more casual for a change.

1388
01:09:55,171 --> 01:09:58,538
This is a look
I like to see on him.

1389
01:09:58,608 --> 01:10:00,007
Not so uptight.
Not so...

1390
01:10:00,076 --> 01:10:02,010
I got to get started here.

1391
01:10:02,078 --> 01:10:03,272
It's wonderful.
It's very good.

1392
01:10:03,346 --> 01:10:05,837
- Be honest with me.
- I'm being honest.

1393
01:10:05,915 --> 01:10:07,246
Would you wear it?

1394
01:10:07,316 --> 01:10:10,410
I like it. I'm so glad
I went with red.

1395
01:10:10,486 --> 01:10:12,420
It looks so good on him.

1396
01:10:12,488 --> 01:10:14,388
It looks good,Jerry.

1397
01:10:14,457 --> 01:10:16,925
- Come on.
- What?

1398
01:10:16,993 --> 01:10:18,722
Take it off and let's go.

1399
01:10:18,794 --> 01:10:19,726
Oh, O.K., fine.

1400
01:10:19,795 --> 01:10:22,127
You want me to take it off?

1401
01:10:22,198 --> 01:10:23,256
Yeah.

1402
01:10:23,332 --> 01:10:25,596
Can't he wear it
for a little while?

1403
01:10:25,668 --> 01:10:27,602
Will you take it off,
please?

1404
01:10:27,670 --> 01:10:29,467
I know he's in a meeting.

1405
01:10:29,539 --> 01:10:33,441
This is an emergency,
and I've got to talk to him.

1406
01:10:33,509 --> 01:10:37,377
You'll interrupt him or I'll come
busting into that meeting.

1407
01:10:37,446 --> 01:10:40,506
No. Forget calling me back.
I'm on my way.

1408
01:10:40,583 --> 01:10:43,711
Why didn't you
just listen to the tape?

1409
01:10:43,786 --> 01:10:45,219
It wasn't that hard...

1410
01:10:45,288 --> 01:10:48,280
a few minutes of your time
to listen to something...

1411
01:10:48,357 --> 01:10:50,791
that I worked
on my whole life.

1412
01:10:50,860 --> 01:10:52,293
Let's go to my office...

1413
01:10:52,361 --> 01:10:55,296
and we'll play
the tape right now.

1414
01:10:55,364 --> 01:10:58,390
Do you know what would
happen if I went there?

1415
01:10:58,467 --> 01:10:59,900
You know, I'm not stupid.

1416
01:10:59,969 --> 01:11:01,402
Nobody's calling you stupid.

1417
01:11:01,470 --> 01:11:03,802
You pulled this off.
That makes you smart.

1418
01:11:03,873 --> 01:11:07,274
You know,Jerry,
I'm going to tell you something.

1419
01:11:07,343 --> 01:11:09,277
Friendship is a two-way street.

1420
01:11:09,345 --> 01:11:12,610
Do you know that?

1421
01:11:12,682 --> 01:11:15,116
And you couldn't
care less about me.

1422
01:11:15,184 --> 01:11:16,617
Am I holding this
till next Shavuot?

1423
01:11:16,686 --> 01:11:18,620
You going to make
some decisions?

1424
01:11:18,688 --> 01:11:21,953
You going to knock off the talking
for two minutes?

1425
01:11:22,024 --> 01:11:23,958
You put the sweater on him.

1426
01:11:24,026 --> 01:11:25,584
Yeah. It took one minute.

1427
01:11:25,661 --> 01:11:28,095
- You have a long night
ahead of you.
- I have something to say.

1428
01:11:28,164 --> 01:11:29,597
You've got enough to say.

1429
01:11:29,665 --> 01:11:31,098
- You're driving me nuts.
-Just a minute.

1430
01:11:31,167 --> 01:11:33,601
Can you be quiet
for one goddamn minute...

1431
01:11:33,669 --> 01:11:36,729
and let me rest
with this gun?

1432
01:11:36,806 --> 01:11:38,740
You're driving me crazy!

1433
01:11:38,808 --> 01:11:41,242
You haven't shut up
since we've walked in.

1434
01:11:41,310 --> 01:11:44,108
This is my house.
This is my domain.

1435
01:11:44,180 --> 01:11:46,671
Jerry is my guest,
and you're my guest.

1436
01:11:46,749 --> 01:11:48,182
And you're lucky to be here.

1437
01:11:48,250 --> 01:11:49,683
You change in my house.

1438
01:11:49,752 --> 01:11:53,188
You get to get your head together
for the show tonight.

1439
01:11:53,255 --> 01:11:54,654
Give me a little break.

1440
01:11:54,724 --> 01:11:57,158
-Shut up.
- Why don't you shut up?

1441
01:11:57,226 --> 01:11:59,524
I listened to you
talk about that sweater.

1442
01:11:59,595 --> 01:12:01,426
Worrying about the sleeves,
the color.

1443
01:12:01,497 --> 01:12:02,930
Did I say anything?

1444
01:12:02,999 --> 01:12:04,432
I made it forJerry...

1445
01:12:04,500 --> 01:12:06,661
and it looks
fabulous on him.

1446
01:12:06,736 --> 01:12:08,169
Whose idea was this anyway?

1447
01:12:08,237 --> 01:12:11,673
If it wasn't for me,
you wouldn't even be here.

1448
01:12:11,741 --> 01:12:15,199
Why didn't you just listen
to the tape when I asked?

1449
01:12:15,277 --> 01:12:17,074
I'm sure you can understand.

1450
01:12:17,146 --> 01:12:20,582
Doing the kind of show I'm doing,
it's mind-boggling.

1451
01:12:20,650 --> 01:12:23,084
There's so much stuff
that comes down...

1452
01:12:23,152 --> 01:12:25,848
you can't keep
your head clear.

1453
01:12:25,921 --> 01:12:28,355
And if that's the case,
I'm wrong.

1454
01:12:28,424 --> 01:12:29,789
You're right.
I'm wrong.

1455
01:12:29,859 --> 01:12:31,292
If I'm wrong, I apologize.

1456
01:12:31,360 --> 01:12:33,294
I'm just a human being...

1457
01:12:33,362 --> 01:12:36,798
with all of the foibles
and all of the traps...

1458
01:12:36,866 --> 01:12:38,299
the show,
the pressure...

1459
01:12:38,367 --> 01:12:39,800
the groupies,
the autograph hounds...

1460
01:12:39,869 --> 01:12:41,302
the crew,
the incompetence...

1461
01:12:41,370 --> 01:12:44,305
those behind-the-scenes
you think are your friends.

1462
01:12:44,373 --> 01:12:46,807
You're not sure if you'll
be there tomorrow...

1463
01:12:46,876 --> 01:12:48,309
because of their incompetence.

1464
01:12:48,377 --> 01:12:50,311
There are wonderful pressures
that make every day...

1465
01:12:50,379 --> 01:12:52,939
a glowing, radiant day in your life.

1466
01:12:53,015 --> 01:12:54,573
It's terrific.

1467
01:12:54,650 --> 01:12:57,517
O.K., if all of
that means nothing...

1468
01:12:57,586 --> 01:13:00,020
if I'm wrong,
in spite of all that...

1469
01:13:00,089 --> 01:13:01,488
then I apologize.

1470
01:13:01,557 --> 01:13:02,649
I'm sorry.

1471
01:13:02,725 --> 01:13:05,216
If you accept my apology...

1472
01:13:05,294 --> 01:13:07,159
I think we should shake hands.

1473
01:13:07,229 --> 01:13:08,662
We'll forget the whole thing.

1474
01:13:08,731 --> 01:13:10,164
I won't press charges.

1475
01:13:10,232 --> 01:13:12,166
You could be
in deep trouble...

1476
01:13:12,234 --> 01:13:16,534
but I will not
press charges.

1477
01:13:16,605 --> 01:13:18,732
That's easy for you to say.

1478
01:13:18,808 --> 01:13:20,241
But I mean it.

1479
01:13:20,309 --> 01:13:21,742
I'll go to the office...

1480
01:13:21,811 --> 01:13:24,245
and tell them all it's a gag.

1481
01:13:24,313 --> 01:13:25,746
They'll understand that.

1482
01:13:25,815 --> 01:13:27,510
If I tell them, they'll buy it.

1483
01:13:27,583 --> 01:13:29,448
Then we'll put the tape on.

1484
01:13:29,518 --> 01:13:32,214
Sit down.
I said, ""sit down.''

1485
01:13:32,288 --> 01:13:33,619
You heard what he said.

1486
01:13:33,689 --> 01:13:36,783
With a gun on him,
he wants to be friends.

1487
01:13:36,859 --> 01:13:39,293
What happens
when he walks out the door?

1488
01:13:39,361 --> 01:13:41,556
What happens then,Jerry?

1489
01:13:41,630 --> 01:13:43,860
You get to his office,
and they jump you.

1490
01:13:43,933 --> 01:13:45,400
Is that what happens,Jerry?

1491
01:13:45,468 --> 01:13:47,902
Not if I tell them not to.

1492
01:13:47,970 --> 01:13:49,904
No one's going to jump you.

1493
01:13:49,972 --> 01:13:52,532
If I tell them to,
they do it.

1494
01:13:52,608 --> 01:13:54,542
No one's going to jump you.

1495
01:13:54,610 --> 01:13:57,807
Now, that's the truth.
Take my word for it.

1496
01:13:57,880 --> 01:14:00,815
If you think
I'm not telling you the truth...

1497
01:14:00,883 --> 01:14:02,316
then don't respond.

1498
01:14:02,384 --> 01:14:05,615
If I'm telling the truth,
let me out of here.

1499
01:14:05,688 --> 01:14:07,656
He gives me his word.

1500
01:14:07,723 --> 01:14:08,815
And what else?

1501
01:14:08,891 --> 01:14:10,552
And what else,Jerry?

1502
01:14:10,626 --> 01:14:16,394
There is nothing else,
just my word.

1503
01:14:16,465 --> 01:14:18,831
Now, isn't my word
good enough?

1504
01:14:22,104 --> 01:14:23,537
I'm sorry,Jerry.

1505
01:14:37,219 --> 01:14:42,555
Suppose we tape him,
he doesn't talk...

1506
01:14:42,625 --> 01:14:44,490
it gets to be 1 1 :30...

1507
01:14:44,560 --> 01:14:46,994
do we put him on
no matter what?

1508
01:14:47,062 --> 01:14:48,495
Go ahead and tape him.

1509
01:14:48,564 --> 01:14:49,997
